  "texts": [
    "Unlike most other solutions that work on virtualizing a single type of accelerator, AVA can virtualize multiple accelerators, including GPUs, TPUs, and FPGAs.",
    "However, the AVA framework is not a generic virtualization support and cannot include any new hardware accelerator (e.g., UPMEM ranks).",
    "In addition, the AVA design targets compute offload accelerators APIs.",
    "It does not provide guest VMs with a virtual representation of the accelerator but with an endpoint that routes communication through the hypervisor.",
    "vPIM, on the other hand, aims to fully virtualize the UPMEM ranks while allowing concurrent utilization by host applications."
  ],
